data.name: previewPictureBox.ToolTip
data.value:
Your image preview for the selected image will appear here.
Click to open a preview window. On Windows, this will be your default photo viewer.
Right-click to copy the image to your clipboard.

data.name: screenshotLabel.ToolTip
data.value: This is the number of screenshots shown in the list below.

data.name: saveAllProgressbar.ToolTip
data.value: This progress bar shows the progress of the current 'Save All' task.

data.name: saveOneBtn.ToolTip
data.value: This button saves the current screenshot to a location of your choosing.

data.name: saveAllBtn.ToolTip
data.value:
This button saves all screenshots in the list to a chosen location.
Compared to 'Turbo' mode, it's slower but shows a preview of the images as they are saved.

data.name: selectFolderBtn.ToolTip
data.value: This button allows you to change the current screenshot directory.

data.name: detectFolderBtn.ToolTip
data.value:
This button attempts to automatically locate your screenshot folder.
Typically this is "My Games/FINAL FANTASY XV/(Steam/Origin)/.../savestorage/snapshot"

data.name: authVerLabel.ToolTip
data.value:
Narod's FFXV Screenshot Grabber.
by Narod

data.name: saveScreenshotDialog.Title
data.value: Choose where to save this screenshot...

data.name: realtimeCheckBox.ToolTip
data.value: Realtime mode allows the utility to automatically save screenshots as the game creates them.

data.name: saveAllTBtn.ToolTip
data.value:
This button saves all screenshots in the list to a chosen location.
It does this in "Turbo" mode, which is very fast but doesn't show previews like the non-Turbo mode does.

data.name: comradesCheckbox.ToolTip
data.value:
Quick switches you to Comrades photos (or base game photos)
You can also achieve this by using 'Select' in the folder options.
